title: For Sale:  Springfield Model 1870 .50-70 Trapdoor Rifle
postcontent: Springfield Model 1870 .50-70 Trapdoor Rifle. The Model 1870, of which only 12,000 examples were manufatured between 1870 and 1873, was the precursor to the Speringfield Model 1873 .45-70 trapdoors of which over 700,000 were manufacturd. The very short service duration and the very small numbers produced, make the Springfield Model 1870 rifle very scarce and highly sought after. On the ther hand, over 700,000 of the subsequent Springfield 1873 .45-70 caliber trapdoors were manufactured.This rifle is in very good condition having recently been restored and is a beautiful and unique display rifle.
